<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Mail::Vacation - implements unix vacation program</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Reimplentation of the unix &#60;B&#62;vacation&#60;/B&#62; program,
with the intention of using various authorisation and control configurations,
eg LDAP.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SYNOPSIS"
>SYNOPSIS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<pre class="sh_perl">  use Mail::Vacation;

  $o_vac  = Mail::Vacation-&#62;new($config) or die(&#34;failed :-(&#34;);

  $o_vac-&#62;start;

  $o_vac-&#62;process($o_mail_internet); 

  $o_vac-&#62;finish;

  $i_isok = $o_vac-&#62;isok;

  @s_msgs = $o_vac-&#62;messages;</pre>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="ABSTRACT"
>ABSTRACT <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Perl implementation of the vacation mail handling program, with the intention of using various authorisation and control configurations, eg LDAP. Logging to syslog.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NOTES"
>NOTES <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Configure this instance in the &#39;vacation.conf&#39; file</p>

<p>Logging is via syslog to /var/log/messages, (make sure syslogd is running!)</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SCRIPTS"
>SCRIPTS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<dl>
<dt><a name='vacation'></a><a name="vacation.pl"
>vacation.pl</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>standard vacation script expecting /home/$user/.vacation message file to operate</p>

<dt><a name='cleanup'></a><a name="cleanup.pl"
>cleanup.pl</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>cleans configurable time-expired repliedtodbdir entries via cron job</p>

<dt><a name='test'></a><a name="test.cgi"
>test.cgi</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>vanilla &#39;hello world&#39; script to test httpd installation against script directory</p>
</dd>
</dl>

